ated during and after World War II that now present themselves in new garb and does so in a clear and concise manner.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aHuman rights. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  aHuman Rights.  aLaw.  aPolitical Science.  aPublic Policy.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812298130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812298130/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK